about.summary: Imputation of incomplete continuous or categorical datasets; Missing values are imputed with a principal component analysis (PCA), a multiple correspondence analysis (MCA) model or a multiple factor analysis (MFA) model; Perform multiple imputation with and in PCA or MCA.

name: r-missmda
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.16" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-missmda
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/missMDA_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/missMDA/missMDA_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: b543b63fb82b79e5b1f07774112159c24bca20a1d0f2f5608a58f4bd9f4faa30

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-factominer
    - r-doparallel
    - r-foreach
    - r-mice
    - r-mvtnorm
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-factominer
    - r-doparallel
    - r-foreach
    - r-mice
    - r-mvtnorm

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('missMDA')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('missMDA')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://husson.github.io/, http://juliejosse.com/
  license: GPL (>= 2)
  summary: Imputation of incomplete continuous or categorical datasets; Missing values are imputed
    with a principal component analysis (PCA), a multiple correspondence analysis (MCA)
    model or a multiple factor analysis (MFA) model; Perform multiple imputation with
    and in PCA or MCA.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - rasmusagren
